The paper deals with the application of variational inference to topic models, which is a popular area of research in machine learning and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
